5:
Are you ready, Murakumo?
Three... two... one!
12: Oh! I think he's got it!
19: Aw, I really thought you had it there.
25:
He critiqued my form when I tried, so 
I figured an expert like Soushiro might 
have a chance.
29:
While I see your logic, I am far from an 
expert, Alk.
30:
I am terribly sorry for yanking at your 
handle, Murakumo. A blade is 
a swordsman's closest companion—
and should be treated with more 
respect than that.
35:
No worries, friend. 
I appreciate you trying.
36:
Given you helped free me from 
Orochi's seal, I thought perhaps my 
blade would accept you as an heir.
41:
Hmm... I get the feeling strength or skill 
alone won't be enough to draw 
Murakumo. We might really need to 
find a familial heir.
44:
We still don't have any leads on who 
his last partner was though, let alone 
his descendants...
48:
That is no fault of yours. If only I could 
remember something—anything—that 
might give us a clue...
53:
I may know something that will trigger 
your memories.
55:
Suizen has been investigating your 
history, and found records of a sword 
that sounds like you, Murakumo.
58: He did? Please, tell me more.
65:
*wheeze* F-finally... we made it to the 
top...
68:
The view is amazing though. 
Murakumo, do you mind if I take 
a quick break and get something to 
eat?
72:
Please, go ahead. No need to hurry—
Ah! The shopkeeper ran away.
...Did I scare him?
78:
The shopkeeper was dumbstruck. Not 
every day you see a boy try to feed 
a sword sweets.
82:
Huh? ...Oh! I, I didn't think of that. I've 
seen undead people eat, so I just 
assumed spirits do too. Now that 
I think of it though, swords don't eat, 
huh?
84:
I do not require food, but I can eat if 
I choose. I appreciate the gesture, Alk.
88:
This feels nostalgic, somehow. I believe 
I was once wielded by a young man 
like you.
90:
I can faintly recall sitting with him, 
eating dango—just like this.
...Yes, he often came to talk, always 
bringing food to share.
93:
Really? What was he like? He must've 
been strong to wield you.
98:
Quite the opposite. He was abysmal 
with a sword, so I always had to take 
care of him.
101: ...Just as he always took care of me.
105:
This looks like the memorial Suizen 
mentioned.
108:
Yes, the energy surrounding it feels 
familiar.
110:
I know the spirit who rests here—he 
was the last person to wield my blade!
113:
This day'll be your last! Ogna 
beeeeam!
115:
Hey! No fair! It's MY turn to be Lord 
Ogna!
118:
Pardon me, little ones. I presume you 
live nearby.
119:
Can you take me to your village's 
strongest warrior? I would like to speak 
with them.
122:
Warrior? You mean like a samurai? We 
haven't got none 'a those 'round here.
125:
None? But what of this memorial? Do 
you know of this man's family?
128:
Uhhh...  Don't think he had none, 
Mister. All I know's he was a super cool 
samurai, but died foreeeever ago. It's 
just us farm-folk in these parts now.
132:
Where'd they come from?! Murakumo, 
watch the kids! I'll handle the 
monsters!
135:
I can deal with the monsters.
...Draw my blade.
147:
If there are no next of kin to inherit me, 
I shall appoint a new partner myself—
you, Alk!
149:
I entrust you with the power to stand 
above all others! Use it wisely!
157:
What are you doing?! My blade has 
ended wars—toppled empires! You 
would throw it aside?!
159:
I don't want to "use" you. I'd rather you 
fought with me than for me!
161:
Besides, I don't know how to wield 
a curved blade anyways. Your sword is 
better off with you!
166:
Ahaha, how am I to counter that?
...Very well, I will keep my blade—and 
entrust you my back.
171:
Perfect! I'll take the ones on this side. 
You better work up an appetite, cause 
I'm getting more of those dango for 
the walk home!
174: You really do remind me of him...
177:
Whether you wield me yourself or not, 
I will not retract my words. Let us fight
—as partners!
